                            <p><a href="http://www.czechcrime.org" target="_blank" title="Czech crime">www.czechcrime.org</a> s a non-for profit, non-governmental initiative of Otevřená společnost, o.p.s.We believe that this website will enhance public debate about the nature of gathering and  recording of crime data and about the ways of its presentation towards public.</p> 
                            <p>Recently, police publishes monthly statistics in complicated and user-unfriendly excel tables. With Czechcrime.org, crime data become available and understandable to anybody who is interested.</p>
                            <p>However, the data published at <a href="http://www.czechcrime.org" target="_blank" title="Czech crime">Czechcrime.org</a> are robust and valid (yet unofficial) source of information about crime in Czech republic. The data can be used under BY-NC-SA Creative Commons license.</p>
                            <p>The institution of <a href="http://www.czechcrime.org" target="_blank" title="Czech crime">Czechcrime.org</a> has been supported by <a href="http://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/about/programs/think-tank-fund" target="_blank" title="Think Tank Fund">Think Tank Fund</a> program <a href="http://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/" title="Open Society Foundations" target="_blank">Open Society Foundations</a>.</p> 
